'''David Alan Grier''' (born [[June 30]], [[1950s#1956|1956]]) is an [[Wikipedia:Americans|American]] actor, voice actor and comedian. He is known for being a cast member on ''[[Wikipedia:In Living Color|In Living Color]]'' and ''[[Wikipedia:Martin (TV series)|Martin]]'' in the 1990s. He later won the [[Wikipedia:Tony Award for Best Featured Actor in a Play|Tony Award for Best Featured Actor in a Play]] at the [[Wikipedia:74th Tony Awards|74th Tony Awards]] for leading the [[Wikipedia:Broadway theatre|Broadway]] revival of ''[[Wikipedia:A Soldier's Play|A Soldier's Play]]''.

In ''[[Star Wars]]'' media, Grier provided additional voices for the radio dramatizations of [[Star Wars (radio)|''Star Wars'']] and [[The Empire Strikes Back (radio)|''The Empire Strikes Back'']].

